Project Overview------------

This project demonstrates an end-to-end data analytics workflow using Python (Pandas) for data cleaning & transformation and SQL for business insights.

Files in this Repository--------------

orders.csv
Raw dataset containing customer orders.

df_orders.csv
Cleaned and transformed version of orders.csv. Data was processed using Pandas (handling missing values, formatting dates, correcting datatypes, etc.).

prj.ipynb
Jupyter Notebook used for the data cleaning and preprocessing steps. This file shows the Python code for transforming orders.csv into df_orders.csv.

sql.sql
SQL script containing analytical queries. These queries include:
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Top selling products & regions

Monthly/Yearly sales trends

Category-wise best performing months

Sub-category growth comparison across years
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Workflow

1. Load the raw dataset (orders.csv).
2. Clean and transform data in Python → output saved as df_orders.csv.
3. Import cleaned data into SQL database.
4. Run advanced SQL queries (sql.sql) to answer business questions.



/////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
E-Commerce Sales Report (PDF Export Explanation)

This report has been generated in Power BI and exported as PDF. It provides a detailed overview of sales, profit, and customer insights across multiple dimensions.

The report includes the following visualizations:

1. Sales by Product ID – shows total sales revenue contribution by each product.
2. Sales by Region – compares sales performance across Central, East, South, and West regions.
3. Profit by Category – highlights profitability in Technology, Furniture, and Office Supplies categories.
4. Profit Margin % by Segment – analyzes margin performance across Consumer, Corporate, and Home Office customer segments.
5. Sales Trend by Day – visualizes daily sales over time for both 2022 and 2023 to identify growth patterns and seasonality.
6. Sales by City – ranks top-performing cities like New York, Los Angeles, Seattle, etc.
7. Sales by Segment – compares total sales share between Consumer, Corporate, and Home Office.
8. Sales by Region & Category (Matrix) – a detailed breakdown showing sales for each category in every region.

